library(ggplot2)
marvel_data <- read.csv("marvel-wikia-data.csv", 
                        na.string = "") # valori mancanti

Analisi univariate

ggplot(data=marvel_data, aes(x=SEX)) +
  geom_bar() +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

ggplot(data=marvel_data, aes(x=SEX, fill = ALIVE)) +
  geom_bar(position = "stack") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

ggplot(data=marvel_data, aes(x=SEX, fill = ALIVE)) +
  geom_bar(position = "dodge") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

ggplot(data=marvel_data, aes(x=SEX, fill = ALIVE)) +
  geom_bar(position = "fill") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

Barplot con dati aggregati

sex_count <- marvel_data %>%
  group_by(SEX) %>%
  summarise(n_personaggi = n())
## Warning: Factor `SEX` contains implicit NA, consider using
## `forcats::fct_explicit_na`
print(sex_count)
## # A tibble: 5 x 2
##   SEX                    n_personaggi
##   <fct>                         <int>
## 1 Agender Characters               45
## 2 Female Characters              3837
## 3 Genderfluid Characters            2
## 4 Male Characters               11638
## 5 <NA>                            854
ggplot(data=sex_count, aes(x=SEX, y=n_personaggi)) +
  geom_col() +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

sex_align_count <- marvel_data %>%
  group_by(SEX, ALIGN) %>%
  summarise(n_personaggi = n())

## Warning: Factor `ALIGN` contains implicit NA, consider using

sex_align_count
